nuclearcraft.particle.alpha.desc: Alpha Particle is another name for the nucleus of helium 4. It is commonly released in the decay of heavy elements like uranium and plutonium.
nuclearcraft.particle.alpha.name: Alpha Particle
nuclearcraft.particle.antialpha.desc: The Anti-Alpha Particle is the antimatter partner of the Alpha Particle.
nuclearcraft.particle.antialpha.name: Anti-Alpha Particle
nuclearcraft.particle.antibottom_quark.d: The Anti-Bottom Quark is the antimatter partner of the Bottom Quark.
nuclearcraft.particle.anticharm_quark.de: The Anti-Charm Quark is the antimatter partner of the Charm Quark.
nuclearcraft.particle.antidelta_minus.de: Anti-Delta - is a baryon containing three Anti-Down Quarks. They quickly decay via the strong force.
nuclearcraft.particle.antidelta_plus_plu: Anti-Delta ++ is a baryon containing three Anti-Up Quarks. They quickly decay via the strong force.
nuclearcraft.particle.antideuteron.desc: The Anti-Deuteron is the antimatter partner of the Deuteron.
nuclearcraft.particle.antideuteron.name: Anti-Deuteron
nuclearcraft.particle.antidown_quark.des: The Anti-Down Quark is the antimatter partner of the Up Down.
nuclearcraft.particle.antihelion.desc: The Anti-Helion is the antimatter partner of the Helion.
nuclearcraft.particle.antihelion.name: Anti-Helion
nuclearcraft.particle.antikaon_naught.de: The Anti-Kaon 0 is a meson with strangeness of -1.
nuclearcraft.particle.antimuon.desc: The Anti-Muon is the antimatter partner of the Muon.
nuclearcraft.particle.antimuon.name: Anti-Muon
nuclearcraft.particle.antineutron.desc: The Anti-Neutron is the antimatter partner of the Neutron.
nuclearcraft.particle.antineutron.name: Anti-Neutron
nuclearcraft.particle.antiproton.desc: The Anti-Proton is the antimatter partner of the Proton.
nuclearcraft.particle.antiproton.name: Anti-Proton
nuclearcraft.particle.antisigma_minus.de: Anti-Sigma Baryons contain one Anti-Strange Quark. They are heavier than Anti-Protons and Anti-Neutrons.
nuclearcraft.particle.antisigma_naught.d: Anti-Sigma Baryons contain one Anti-Strange Quark. They are heavier than Anti-Protons and Anti-Neutrons.
nuclearcraft.particle.antisigma_plus.des: Anti-Sigma Baryons contain one Anti-Strange Quark. They are heavier than Anti-Protons and Anti-Neutrons.
The Anti-Strange Quark is the antimatter partner of the Strange Quark.
nuclearcraft.particle.antitau.desc: The Anti-Tau is the antimatter partner of the Tau.
nuclearcraft.particle.antitau.name: Anti-Tau
nuclearcraft.particle.antitop_quark.desc: The Anti-Top Quark is the antimatter partner of the Top Quark.
nuclearcraft.particle.antitop_quark.name: Anti-Top Quark
nuclearcraft.particle.antitriton.desc: The Anti-Triton is the antimatter partner of the Triton.
nuclearcraft.particle.antitriton.name: Anti-Triton
nuclearcraft.particle.antiup_quark.desc: The Anti-Up Quark is the antimatter partner of the Up Quark.
nuclearcraft.particle.antiup_quark.name: Anti-Up Quark
nuclearcraft.particle.boron_ion.desc: A Boron atom with one electron missing.
nuclearcraft.particle.boron_ion.name: Boron Ion
nuclearcraft.particle.bottom_eta.desc: Eta Mesons are flavorless mesons meaning their flavor numbers like strangeness and isospin are 0.
nuclearcraft.particle.bottom_eta.name: Bottom Eta Meson
nuclearcraft.particle.bottom_quark.desc: The Bottom Quark is a very heavy version of the Down Quark.
nuclearcraft.particle.bottom_quark.name: Bottom Quark
nuclearcraft.particle.calcium_48_ion.des: A Calcium-48 atom with one electron missing. This is a particularly neutron rich atom useful for creating Super heavy elements.
nuclearcraft.particle.charm_quark.desc: The Charm Quark is a heavy version of the Up Quark.
nuclearcraft.particle.charm_quark.name: Charm Quark
nuclearcraft.particle.charmed_eta.desc: Eta Mesons are flavorless mesons meaning their flavor numbers like strangeness and isospin are 0.
nuclearcraft.particle.charmed_eta.name: Charmed Eta Meson
nuclearcraft.particle.delta_minus.desc: Delta - is a baryon containing three Down Quarks. They quickly decay via the strong force.
nuclearcraft.particle.delta_minus.name: Delta -
nuclearcraft.particle.delta_plus_plus.de: Delta ++ is a baryon containing three Up Quarks. They quickly decay via the strong force.
nuclearcraft.particle.deuteron.desc: The Deuteron is the nucleus of a Deuterium Atom.
nuclearcraft.particle.deuteron.name: Deuteron
nuclearcraft.particle.down_quark.desc: The Down Quark is the second lightest quark. Up and Down quarks combine to form Protons and Neutrons
nuclearcraft.particle.down_quark.name: Down Quark
nuclearcraft.particle.electron.desc: The Electron is lightest charged lepton. It is commonly found in orbitals around nuclei, forming atoms.
nuclearcraft.particle.electron.name: Electron
nuclearcraft.particle.electron_antineutr: The Electron Antineutrino is the antimatter partner of the Electron Neutrino.
The Electron Neutrino is the neutrino partner of the Electron.
nuclearcraft.particle.eta.desc: Eta Mesons are flavourless mesons meaning their flavor numbers like strangeness and isospin are 0.
nuclearcraft.particle.eta.name: Eta Meson
nuclearcraft.particle.eta_prime.desc: Eta Mesons are flavorless mesons meaning their flavor numbers like strangeness and isospin are 0.
nuclearcraft.particle.eta_prime.name: Eta Prime Meson
nuclearcraft.particle.glueball.desc: Glueballs are particle made entirely out of gluons.
nuclearcraft.particle.glueball.name: Glueball
nuclearcraft.particle.gluon.desc: Gluons are the carries of the strong force. The strong force is what keeps quarks bound together to create composite particles like protons and neutrons.
nuclearcraft.particle.gluon.name: Gluon
nuclearcraft.particle.helion.desc: The Helion is the nucleus of a Helium-3 Atom.
nuclearcraft.particle.helion.name: Helion
nuclearcraft.particle.higgs_boson.desc: The Higgs Boson is the boson of the Higgs Field which is responsible for giving particles their mass.
nuclearcraft.particle.higgs_boson.name: Higgs Boson
nuclearcraft.particle.kaon_minus.desc: The Kaon - is a meson with strangeness of -1.
nuclearcraft.particle.kaon_minus.name: Kaon -
nuclearcraft.particle.kaon_naught.desc: The Kaon 0 is a meson with strangeness of 1.
nuclearcraft.particle.kaon_naught.name: Kaon 0
nuclearcraft.particle.kaon_plus.desc: The Kaon + is a meson with strangeness of 1.
nuclearcraft.particle.kaon_plus.name: Kaon +
nuclearcraft.particle.muon.desc: The Muon is basically a heavy electron.
nuclearcraft.particle.muon.name: Muon
The Muon Antineutrino is the antimatter partner of the Muon Neutrino.
nuclearcraft.particle.muon_neutrino.desc: The Muon Neutrino is the neutrino partner of the Muon.
nuclearcraft.particle.muon_neutrino.name: Muon Neutrino
nuclearcraft.particle.neutron.desc: The Neutron is a Nucleon along with the Protons make up the nucleus of atoms. The Neutron is used in nuclear fission to split fissile nuclei.
nuclearcraft.particle.neutron.name: Neutron
nuclearcraft.particle.none.name: None
nuclearcraft.particle.photon.desc: Photons are the particles that make up light. They are the carries of the electromagnetic force. High energy Photons are called gamma rays.
nuclearcraft.particle.photon.name: Photon
nuclearcraft.particle.pion_minus.desc: Pions are the particles that are responsible for holding nuclei together. Although not colored themselves they distribute the "residual" strong force to keep nuclei together.
nuclearcraft.particle.pion_minus.name: Pion -
nuclearcraft.particle.pion_naught.desc: Pions are the particles that are responsible for holding nuclei together. Although not colored themselves they distribute the "residual" strong force to keep nuclei together.
nuclearcraft.particle.pion_naught.name: Pion 0
nuclearcraft.particle.pion_plus.desc: Pions are the particles that are responsible for holding nuclei together. Although not colored themselves they distribute the "residual" strong force to keep nuclei together.
nuclearcraft.particle.pion_plus.name: Pion +
nuclearcraft.particle.positron.desc: The positron is the Antimatter particle of the electron. When a electron and positron meet the annihilate resulting in all there mass being converted into energy in the form of 2 gamma rays.
nuclearcraft.particle.positron.name: Positron
nuclearcraft.particle.proton.desc: The Proton is a Nucleon along with the Neutron make up the nucleus of atoms.
nuclearcraft.particle.proton.name: Proton
nuclearcraft.particle.sigma_minus.desc: Sigma Baryons contain one Strange Quark. They are heavier than Protons and Neutrons.
nuclearcraft.particle.sigma_minus.name: Sigma -
nuclearcraft.particle.sigma_naught.desc: Sigma Baryons contain one Strange Quark. They are heavier than Protons and Neutrons.
nuclearcraft.particle.sigma_naught.name: Sigma 0
nuclearcraft.particle.sigma_plus.desc: Sigma Baryons contain one Strange Quark. They are heavier than Protons and Neutrons.
nuclearcraft.particle.sigma_plus.name: Sigma +
nuclearcraft.particle.strange_quark.desc: The Strange Quark is a heavy version of the Down Quark.
nuclearcraft.particle.strange_quark.name: Strange Quark
nuclearcraft.particle.tau.desc: The Tau is basically a really heavy electron
nuclearcraft.particle.tau.name: Tau
nuclearcraft.particle.tau_antineutrino.d: The Tau Antineutrino is the antimatter partner of the Tau Neutrino.
nuclearcraft.particle.tau_neutrino.desc: The Tau Neutrino is the neutrino partner of the Tau.
nuclearcraft.particle.tau_neutrino.name: Tau Neutrino
nuclearcraft.particle.top_quark.desc: The Top Quark is a very heavy version of the Up Quark.
nuclearcraft.particle.top_quark.name: Top Quark
nuclearcraft.particle.triton.desc: The Triton is the nucleus of a Tritium Atom.
nuclearcraft.particle.triton.name: Triton
nuclearcraft.particle.up_quark.desc: The Up Quark is the lightest quark. Up and Down quarks combine to form Protons and Neutrons
nuclearcraft.particle.up_quark.name: Up Quark
nuclearcraft.particle.w_minus_boson.desc: The Z and W bosons are the carries of the weak force. The weak force is what allows some particles to decay and is responsible for beta decay.
nuclearcraft.particle.w_minus_boson.name: W- Boson

tooltip.nc.bearing.desc: Connects the rotor shaft to the turbine wall and dynamo. Must cover the full area of each end of the shaft.
tooltip.nc.blade.desc: Converts the energy of the oncoming fluid flow into rotational energy in the rotor shaft. The expansion coefficient is larger than unity, so the volume of the fluid flow will increase each time it passes through a set. Must be placed in complete sets of four coplanar groups extending from the turbine shaft to the wall. Each blade block can process up to %s of oncoming fluid.
